## How we track work

We keep the project's plan in two always-current files in the repository rather than only in a tracker, so the plan is portable and survives any one tool. The `ROADMAP.md` checklist is the assignable, source-of-truth list of what this level still owes and who owns it, and `NEXT-STEPS.md` is the short narrative handoff memo for a reader who will not open a board. <!-- IF:PROJECT -->For shared, assignable tracking, those same tasks are mirrored onto the project's GitHub Project board, where the team plans across board, table, and roadmap views.<!-- /IF -->

